[size=4][b]Heads-up[/b][/size]

[size=3]The extra quick-craft buttons you can see in the screenshots and videos on this page aren't part of Queue Everything — they come from my other mod, [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/59]Max Buttons Redux[/url]. Install it alongside if you want the same look.[/size]

[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Turns the craft window into a proper queueing interface and (optionally) converts hand-crafts into idle auto-crafts you can walk away from.[/size]

[size=3][b]Queueing[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Queue almost any craft[/b] — if a craft can be run once, it can now be queued multiple times. Some built-in exclusions cover items known to break when queued (buildings, graves, one-off quest items).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Live totals[/b] — when you change the queue quantity, the craft-time, fuel, and energy numbers update on-screen to reflect the real total, not the single-craft values.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-select highest quality[/b] — crafts that pick between multiple tiers of an ingredient (e.g. carrots i/ii/iii) default to the highest you have in stock. Exception: dinner recipes (vanilla handles those quirkily).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-max toggles[/b] — separate options for "multi-quality" and "normal" crafts to automatically fill the queue with as many as your materials allow when you open a craft.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Controller focus[/b] — on controller, expanding a multi-craft auto-focuses the big "Craft Now" button so you can trigger it without fishing for the right input.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Auto-craft (opt-in per workbench)[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3]Convert hand crafts at specific workbenches into timer-based auto-crafts you can queue up and walk away from. [b]The master toggle is on by default but every per-workbench toggle starts off[/b] — the mod does nothing to your crafting until you enable the benches you want. Toggles apply live, no restart.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Supported workbenches (independent toggles):[/b][/size]
[size=3]- Alchemy — alchemy workbench, mortar, survey station
- Cooking — cooking table, tavern kitchen
- Study — study desks, book-writing table
- Metalwork — anvil, hammer station, jewelry bench
- Morgue — body prep, autopsy table, packing table
- Carpentry — sawhorse, chopping spot, carpenter's workbench, beam gantry
- Sermons — church pulpit (removes per-sermon energy cost)
- Printing — printing press, paper press
- Winemaking — vine press
- Pottery — potter's wheel
- Misc — any other hand crafts that don't fit the groups above (e.g. benches added by a future game update)[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Trade-off[/b] — auto-crafted recipes run on a longer timer than hand crafting and, by default, halve red/green/blue research-point outputs (blood, fat, skin, heart, intestine). It's convenience for a cost; turn off "Half Research Point Outputs" under Balance if you want full yields.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Balance tweaks (optional)[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Half Fire Requirements[/b] — halves the fuel each fire craft needs across the board. Independent of the research-point halving above.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Force Multi Craft[/b] — makes almost any craft queue-able even if it isn't normally. A safety list still excludes buildings, graves, and other placements that would break.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Other[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu update notice[/b] — flags when a newer version of this mod (or other mods in my collection) is on Nexus. Click an entry to open the mod's page. Opt-out via the "Check for Updates" setting.[/size]
[*][size=3]If a specific craft breaks when queued and you'd like it added to the safety list, grab the diagnostic log the mod writes and send it my way with a description of what went wrong.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/59]Max Buttons Redux[/url] — the Min/Max buttons you see in this page's screenshots. Install alongside if you want one-click minimum or maximum fills.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] — speeds up crafting across the board. QE's live totals show the adjusted time when it's installed.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — halves energy, gratitude, and sanity costs. QE's live totals show the reduced energy when it's installed.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — one shared inventory across all workstations. Essential for anyone auto-crafting; the shared pool feeds every bench.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multipliers for drops, craft outputs, and research points. Pairs well with the halving trade-off above.[/size]
[/list]

